`trList` contains the `&lt;tr&gt;` with the headers, which doesn&#39;t have `&lt;td&gt;` tags so in the first `for` iteration `tdList` is empty and `tdList.get(index)` throws `IndexOutOfBoundsException`.

You can iterate by index instead

    for (int i = 1 ; i &lt; trList.size() ; i++) {
        tdList = trList.get(i).findElements(By.tagName(&quot;td&quot;));
        cell = tdList.get(index);
        columnCells.add(cell);
    }

Or ship first item

    for (WebElement tr : trList.subList(1, trList.size())) {
        tdList = tr.findElements(By.tagName(&quot;td&quot;));
        cell = tdList.get(index);
        columnCells.add(cell);
    }

